========================================================================
BUGS FIXED (all verified with 0 issues)
========================================================================

1. PIO TYPE MISMATCH — root cause of 171 MPAS remap issues
   pio_initdecomp(PIO_REAL) + pio_write_darray(real(r8)) garbled output.
   Fix: convert to real(4) before write in both MPAS components.

2. FILL-VALUE ARCHITECTURE (apply_masked)
   Old approach zeroed fills + normalized by frac_b -> diluted coastal
   values, land=0 instead of fill. New approach: pack validity mask as
   extra level in SpMV, normalize by valid_frac = sum(w_j * mask_j).
   SHR_FILL_VALUE = 1e20 (shared constant, matches cam_history).

3. SOURCE-SIDE FILL VALUES
   MPAS-SI: iceThicknessMean, surfaceTemperatureMean, airStress set to
   fillValue at ice-free cells (was 0.0, caused ice-edge leakage).
   MPAS-O: sst/sss/heatflux/OHC/FWC/KE set to fillValue at land cells.

4. VCOARSEN ARRAY STRIDE MISMATCH — root cause of EAM T_1..T_8 artifacts
   shr_vcoarsen_avg_cols declares field(ncol,nlev) but received
   src_field(pcols,pver). When ncol<pcols (14 vs 15 in some chunks),
   levels k>1 read wrong memory. Fix: pass src_field(1:ncol,:).

5. REGISTER_VAR DUPLICATE — PIO "name in use" errors
   MPAS framework calls init twice. register_var now skips duplicates.

6. REVIEW IMPROVEMENTS (from reconciliation)
   - Declaration order fix in shr_vcoarsen_mod (portability)
   - Scientific notation d/D parsing + . before exponent in shr_derived_mod
   - Depth bound iostat error handling + monotonicity validation
   - nCoarsenLevels > nFmeDepthLevels bounds check
   - send_local_cell==0 upgraded from WARN to CRIT (fatal on bad map file)
   - PIO write error propagation in both MPAS horiz remap modules

